You can use rpc_toolkit/pe_rpc_if_scraper to statically parse interfaces in a binary file. Run the following command in Python:
python pe_rpc_scraper.py <binary>

Then you will get the output json file like the following:

```
{
  "RPC-Server.exe": {
    "d6b1ad2b-b550-4729-b6c2-1651f58480c3": {
      "number_of_functions": 2,
      "functions_pointers": [
        "0x1400016f0",
        "0x1400017c0"
      ],
      "function_names": [
        "func1",
        "func2"
      ],
      "role": "server",
      "flags": "0x6000000",
      "interface_address": "0x14001d220"
    }
  }
}

```
